    "description" : {
      "en" : "DAIMO is an integration profile that connects DCAT-AP, MLDCAT-AP, ODRL, PROV-O, and the Dataspace Protocol (DSP, as operationalised by Eclipse EDC) to support publication, discovery, invocation, execution traceability, and contextualised evaluation of AI model assets exchanged in data spaces. The edc: namespace is used only for EDC-specific extensions (e.g., ParticipantContext) not yet standardised in DSP."
